body_html: @saudet I'm trying to build a copy of the JavaCPP wrappers, but it seems that due to the rapid rate of change of the tensorflow source they are not compatible with either the 0.6.0 release or today's master branch. Would it be possible to update them with a pointer to the exact tensorflow commit/version they were tested with?
